creator: George MacDonald
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 17 recordings of Bell Upon Organ by George MacDonald. This was an extended Weekly Poetry project started on July 8, 2104. Read in English by Andrew K Waugh; Anders Stigö; Bruce Kachuk; Claudia Salto; David Lawrence; debolee; EddS; Jason Mills; J Korth; Julia Niedermaier; John Sercel; Kimberly Hirsh; Lee Ann Howlett; Leonard Wilson; Mgilbert; Rosslyn Carlyle and SkyAlbatross. George MacDonald was a Scottish author, poet, and Christian minister. He was a pioneering figure in the field of fantasy literature and the mentor of fellow writer Lewis Carroll. His writings have been cited as a major literary influence by many notable authors including W. H. Auden, C. S. Lewis, J. R. R. Tolkien, Walter de la Mare, E. Nesbit and Madeleine L'Engle. (Summary form Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (10MB)
